--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 How to load and install Numerics:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---++ Required external libraries

   * blas / lapack
      * actual version used with the platform : 3.0
      * location : http://www.netlib.org/

---++ Optional external libraries

   * cppunit
      * actual version used with the platform: 1.10.2
      * last version : 1.10.2
      * known problems : none
      * location : http://cppunit.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/moin.cgi

---++ Getting the sources

   * Through the svn server (acess required)
       svn checkout svn+ssh://user@scm.gforge.inria.fr/svn/siconos
       for more explanation see http://gforge.inria.fr/scm/?group_id=9

   * Download the source packages on the Gforge   

---++ INSTALL 

in Numerics directory:
	
	- ./autogen.sh
	- ./configure --prefix="the path where you want to install the platform" --other_options
	- make
	- make install (default install location: /usr/local) 
	- make check (optional) : to run tests	
	- make doc (optional)  : to generate Doxygen documentation

for more details on configure options, type configure --help. 
      
   * If you have a local installation of an external library, you can give its path to configure with the option --with-[library name]. You can get the possible options typing = ./configure --help. 

